<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Access the admin panel</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to the admin panel</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Add <code>/admin</code> to your FixMyStreet URL (e.g., <code>https://[your-url].cloudfront.net/admin</code>).
      You must be signed in with the admin credentials from Step 1.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>View the admin dashboard</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The admin dashboard shows an overview of the system including:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Total number of reports and their status breakdown</li>
      <li>Recent reports requiring attention</li>
      <li>System configuration and council settings</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Browse reports from the admin view</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click on <strong>"Reports"</strong> in the admin navigation to see all reports in a searchable,
      sortable table. This view is designed for council officers who need to manage a high volume
      of reports efficiently.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

