<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What to explore in the admin panel</h3>

<div class="ndx-admin-features">
  <div class="ndx-admin-feature">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Report management</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      View individual reports with full details including location data, citizen information,
      category, and complete update history. Council officers can change status, reassign
      categories, and add internal notes that are not visible to the public.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-admin-feature">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Category configuration</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      See how report categories are configured. In a production deployment, councils can
      customise categories to match their service structure, set up auto-routing rules,
      and configure response templates for common issues.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-admin-feature">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">User management</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      Browse the list of registered users. The demo includes 15 simulated citizen accounts
      who have created the 260 demo reports. In production, this would show real residents
      and their reporting history.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-admin-feature">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Council body settings</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      View the NDX Demo Council configuration including contact details, area boundaries,
      and service settings. Multi-tier councils (e.g., district and county) can configure
      report routing based on category and location.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-inset-text govuk-!-margin-top-4">
  <p class="govuk-body">
    <strong>What to notice:</strong> The admin panel separates operational report management
    from system configuration. Service teams use the council dashboard (Step 4) for day-to-day
    work, while the admin panel is used for system setup and oversight.
  </p>
</div>

{# Troubleshooting #}
<details class="govuk-details govuk-!-margin-top-6">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      Troubleshooting: Cannot access /admin
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    <p class="govuk-body">If you see "access denied" or a blank page at /admin:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Make sure you are signed in with the admin credentials, not a regular citizen account</li>
      <li>Try signing out and back in again</li>
      <li>Check the URL is correct — it should be <code>/admin</code> not <code>/admin/</code> with a trailing slash on some configurations</li>
      <li>Clear your browser cache and try again in a private/incognito window</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

